--- In nbwrpg@y..., dewboy30816@y... wrote:
> The shuttle continues to plumet.  It hits in the jungle hard.  The 
> DNA scanners activate and 3 beast modes are chosen.  A brown horse, 
a 
> grey horse, and a Rhesus Monkey.
> 
> Brown Horse: Hey not bad. From now on you guys can call me Mustex.
> 
> Grey Horse:  Just call me Stallex.
> 
> Mustex:  Hey what do you want to be called.
> 
> Monkey:  We're more animal now than Machine.  And like animals we 
> abandoned our friends at the outpost.  Why fancy up what we are.  
> Just call me Rhesus.
> 
> OOC: The question of what happened to Stallex still applies even 
> though I changed the back story.
> 
> Rhesus:  I developed a little something I called hover-cycles.  They 
> can go at speeds of up to 200 mph.  Thought you might like to know.
> 
> Rhesus presses a button and 3 come out of the storage room.  He then 
> looks at the readouts of the satalite.
> 
> Rhesus:  The biggest energon deposite is occupied and far away.  But 
> there is a fair sized one about 25 miles south of here. I think I 
can 
> still get enough thrust to get the shuttle there, but not to land 
> it.  Believe me when this is over salvage will be the only use for 
> this shuttle.So we better take the hover-cycles.
> 
> Rhesus launches it toward the deposit (no one touch it it's mine) 
and 
> they take off on the cycles.
